			<CASNumber>-</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sodium hydroxide (NaOH), also known as caustic soda or lye, is a corrosive white crystalline solid that contains the sodium cation and the hydroxide anion. It readily absorbs moisture until it dissolves. It is the most widely used industrial alkali and is often used in drain and oven cleaners. Sodium hydroxide is a co-product of chlorine production. It is a highly versatile substance used in a variety of manufacturing processes. In 1807, Sir Humphry Davy became the first to prepare sodium in its elemental form, applying electrolysis to fused sodium hydroxide.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氢氧化钠（NaOH）又称烧碱或碱液，是一种具有腐蚀性的白色结晶固体，含有钠阳离子和氢氧根阴离子。它很容易吸收水分，直至溶解。它是使用最广泛的工业碱，常用于下水道和烤箱清洁剂。氢氧化钠是氯生产的副产品。它是一种用途广泛的物质，可用于各种生产工艺。1807 年，汉弗莱-戴维爵士通过电解熔融氢氧化钠，首次制备出元素形式的钠。</common:generalComment>
